episodes.title: Openings
episodes.plot: Sent to an orphanage at age 9, Beth develops an uncanny knack for chess and a growing dependence on the green tranquilizers given to the children.

episodes.title: Exchanges
episodes.plot: Suddenly plunged into a confusing new life in suburbia, teenage Beth studies her high school classmates and hatches a plan to enter a chess tournament.

episodes.title: Doubled Pawns
episodes.plot: The trip to Cincinnati launches Beth and her mother into a whirlwind of travel and press coverage. Beth sets her sights on the U.S. open in Las Vegas.

episodes.title: Middle Game
episodes.plot: Russian class opens the door to a new social scene. In Mexico City, Beth meets the intimidating Borgov, while her mother cozies up with a pen pal.

episodes.title: Fork
episodes.plot: Back home in Kentucky, a shaken Beth reconnects with a former opponent who offers to help sharpen her game ahead of the U.S. Championship.

episodes.title: Adjournment
episodes.plot: After training with Benny in New York, Beth heads to Paris for her rematch with Borgov. But a wild night sends her into a self-destructive spiral.

episodes.title: End Game
episodes.plot: A visit from an old friend forces Beth to reckon with her past and rethink her priorities, just in time for the biggest match of her life.
